technical_skills: Job Req #: 17-03476 Job Description: Business Operations Associate Location: San Rafael, CA Position Type: Contract **please note, I am only able to work on a W2 basis Key Responsibilities: Entry level position focused on supporting team efforts in the development of site budgets, amending site budgets and coordinating Clinical Trial Agreement activities with sites and CROs. The Associate will work with budget templates, gather budget related data to support negotiations and work with sites and CROs to answer budget related queries. Support the development and implementation key functional projects focused on improving effectiveness or efficiency of operations. Support team efforts in the following activities, including: o Budget Development o Developing study budget template and obtaining study team approval o Using benchmark pricing database (Grants Manager), historical price data to determine budget line item costs o Calculating acceptable negotiation parameters for all key budget line items (high, mid, low) that are in line with and support overall financial goals o Budget Negotiation o Providing rationale for budget line items and promptly respond to any site or CRO queries regarding budget items o Tracking communication and status of all site budget development, budget amendments and budget negotiations o Ongoing Budget maintenance Build relationships with Study Teams, CRO, and sites to maintain awareness of any changes that may impact budgets or site and/or vendor contracting. Attend study team meetings/CRO calls to gather information that may impact budget development and management. Update site budgets based on protocol amendments. Clinical Trial Agreements. Assist in the maintenance of the contract database. Support CCG and BizOps process, SOP, and work instruction development and improvement projects. Qualifications: Expected to demonstrate foundational communication, planning and prioritization, teamwork and proactivity competencies.  Developing competence in key technical competencies such as Site Budget and Contract Management and Business Processes and Technology. The ability to effectively use key productivity tools such as excel and quickly grasping and following Clinical Contracts and Grants processes. Understanding the structure and basic legal terms of CTAs. Demonstrating basic understanding of how investigator site services/procedures drive CTA financial budgets. Understanding site budget formats, templates and required content. A demonstrated ability to understand and apply basic finance, accounting and procurement principles. About Ascent: The Ascent Services Group (ASG) is a nationally recognized technology staffing and consulting firm whose fundamental business is providing staffing services to Small, Medium, and Large Enterprise clients in our core market verticals: Financial Services, Healthcare, Technology and Life Sciences. As consultants for ASG, you will have access to many of the top clients within the industries we serve. Our goal is to deliver innovative talent through proven best practices and effective resource optimization. Become one of ASG s candidates and experience the difference! IND05
